# GATES — go/no-go decision log

The investigation advances phase-by-phase. Each gate has a **condition** that
must be true to proceed, a **current status**, and the **evidence** that settled
it. Update the status line and append to the history when a gate's state changes.
Cross-reference the logbook entry that moved it.

Status values: `OPEN` (not yet evaluable) · `BLOCKED` (condition failing, work
needed) · `PASSED` (condition met, may proceed) · `FAILED` (terminal — project
stops or pivots).

A gate marked **(HARD)** can terminate the project if it fails — give it the
most rigorous condition and the most evidence.

